 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Alaaraaf</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> A coupla things to add to Usul's comments about mixing and matching Fear & Root:</P><P><img src=icon_smile_big.gif border=0 align=middle>  Root <i>sorta</i> overwrites Fear.<BR>A rooted mob will beat the bejeesus outta it's nearest target, until the root breaks.  When the Root breaks, it'll resume it's usual behaviour and run screaming and cryin' for it's mom!<BR>There is an additional aspect to this effect that you might be able to use to your advantage.  <i>(And it's handy to know anyhow!)</i>  A Rooted mob will beat on it's closest target.  Hate seems almost irrelevant in this, although I haven't actually tested this in any useful way.  But, this gives you a very simple means of controlling who the mob is beating on.</P><P><img src=icon_smile_big.gif border=0 align=middle>  Root plus Fear allows you to Fear kite in a confined space!<BR>I used to use this on Seafury Cyclopses, while hunting Gornit.  <i>(While waiting for the AC camp to free up.  *Sigh*)</i>  Seafuries wander their island pretty freely.  They can be hunted in the mid forties, but the DoTs you have won't kill them particularly quickly.  And, if you let a clops make it very far up the hill, all his friends will come and help him out.  <BR>By Rooting your opponent, while the DoT chews 'em up, you can stop 'em wandering off too far.  This is particularly useful, if you're trying to hunt two at a time, or playing with Fear in a dungeon!  (In general, Fearing in a dungeon is insanely dangerous! Be sure to give it a go.  *Grin*)<BR><i>Important note:  If you Root a caster, they <b>will</b> dump their spells on you!)</i></P><P><img src=icon_smile_big.gif border=0 align=middle>  Hungry Earth is <b>always</b> better than Root, against undead!<BR>If you're hunting undeads, Hungry Earth is the way to go.  Even at higher levels, when you have a whole selection of Root variants!  <i>(Oki, maybe not in every instance.  But, I'm yet to come across a situation where this isn't the case.)</i>  The Sun Revenants in the Scarlet Desert will break normal roots horrifically quickly, but Hungry Earth is pretty Efficaceous!</P><P>Anywho...</P><P>AlAaraaf.</P><P></P><P> </font></td>
